  <shortDescription><![CDATA[<p>On Norway’s mainland coast in Trøms county, north of the Arctic Circle and close to the Swedish border, the harbour town of Narvik is surrounded by stunning natural scenery, including the ‘Skjomtind’ mountain, named ‘The Sleeping Queen’ after Queen Victoria! Narvik is also home to 6,000 year old rock carvings, a vibrant shopping area, and several museums documenting the town’s turbulent history.</p>]]></shortDescription>
